'''Flash training''', also called '''flash learning''' or '''flash instruction''', was the technique of using [[Hologram/Legends|holographic]] flashes to instruct young [[Cloning/Legends|clones]] during their growth period. The process enabled a clone to accumulate knowledge, skills, and competencies at an accelerated rate.

==History==
During the [[Cloning/Legends|development]] stage of the [[Grand Army of the Republic/Legends|Grand Army of the Republic]], the newly created [[Clone trooper/Legends|clone troopers]] were first educated in weapons handling and tactics before moving on to simulations, drills, and live-fire exercises.<ref name="EGW">''[[The Essential Guide to Warfare]]''</ref> A special detachment of [[Clone commando/Legends|elite clones]] was also given flash instruction during the initial stage of their basic training.<ref name="SWRC">''[[Star Wars: Republic Commando]]''</ref> In the late period of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] [[Republic Military/Legends|Military]] deployed millions of additional clone [[Trooper/Legends|troopers]], fully grown in a year by [[Arkanian Microtechnologies]] on [[Centax-2/Legends|Centax-2]] with the use of [[Spaarti cloning cylinder|Spaarti technology]]. Due to the new clones' extremely fast growth cycle, they used different learning technique called [[flash pumping]],<ref name="EGtW:AC7">{{SW|url=news/the-essential-guide-to-warfare-authors-cut-part-7-the-grand-army-of-the-republic|series=Star Wars: The Essential Guide to Warfare Author's Cut|text=Part 7 &mdash; The Grand Army of the Republic}}</ref> which composed the whole of their basic training. In combat, the [[Arkanian/Legends|Arkanian]] clones displayed poor marksmanship and a lack of strategy,<ref name="Order66">''[[Order 66: A Republic Commando Novel]]''</ref> effectively making them subpar [[Soldier/Legends|soldiers]] in comparison to their [[Kaminoan/Legends|Kaminoan]]-bred counterparts.<ref name="EGW" />

[[Memory flash]]es, a variant of flash training, were used for imparting the knowledge and experience of a [[Clone template/Legends|prime clone]] into a clone subject. A side effect of the memory imprints, however, was that they could destabilize a clone's mental health. By obtaining the memories of another person's life, the clone could fall into an identity crisis, making the clone unable to distinguish its own experiences from the progenitor's memories. Ultimately, the confusion could drive the clone into a state of [[Clone madness|insanity]].<ref name="TFUII">''[[Star Wars: The Force Unleashed II]]''</ref>

